<subSubSection id="C3136563FFAFAE68AEDF6552F89CF86B" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB636E8FFAFAE68AEDF6552F89CF86B" blockId="6.[151,1437,1802,2045]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AEDF6552FB5AF8B3" bold="true" box="[151,274,1802,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFAFAE68AF526554FB28F8B3" authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[282,352,1804,1829]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AF526554FB28F8B3" box="[282,352,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AF206553FBF1F8B3" bold="true" box="[360,441,1803,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E5781FFAFAE68AF206553FBF1F8B3" box="[360,441,1803,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possesses lateral pronotal carinae terminating on the ventral margin of the prothorax, a character shared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFAFAE68AFC26577FBABF8DF" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[394,483,1839,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myndus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AFC26577FBABF8DF" box="[394,483,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myndus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but lacks the denticle of the forecoxae (
<figureCitation id="13322A6DFFAFAE68ADD16577F994F8DF" box="[921,988,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,997,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,995,1955]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 2. Front leg of adult male Myxia gen. n. belinda sp. n. demonstrating lack of denticle on forecoxa (FC), location where denticle is present in Myndus in white circle." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557841/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), a feature shared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFAFAE68AA946577FF07F8DF" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[1244,1359,1839,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AA946577FF07F8DF" box="[1244,1359,1839,1865]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Tegulae evident and tibiae of hind legs lack spines (tribal feature of 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFAFAE68AD07650BF9FBF8F8" authorityName="Muir" authorityYear="1922" box="[847,947,1875,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Oecleini">Oecleini</taxonomicName>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFAFAE68AA75650CFECBF8FB" authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[1085,1155,1876,1901]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AA75650CFECBF8FB" box="[1085,1155,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AAC1650BFE9FF8FB" bold="true" box="[1161,1239,1875,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E5781FFAFAE68AAC1650BFE9FF8FB" box="[1161,1239,1875,1901]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be diagnosed from 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFAFAE68AE9E652FFB01F807" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[214,329,1911,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AE9E652FFB01F807" box="[214,329,1911,1937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFAFAE68AFCB652FFB94F807" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[387,476,1911,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myndus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68AFCB652FFB94F807" box="[387,476,1911,1937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myndus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the overall form of the gonostyli. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFAFAE68ADE46520F9BAF807" authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[940,1010,1912,1937]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68ADE46520F9BAF807" box="[940,1010,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFAFAE68ADB3652FFE03F807" bold="true" box="[1019,1099,1911,1937]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E5781FFAFAE68ADB3652FFE03F807" box="[1019,1099,1911,1937]" pageId="6" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, the gonostyli appear distally bifid, possessing a dorsal process near the terminus of each gonostylus in lateral view pointing dorsad and in ventral view, and a lateral tooth on the inner margin with an acute apex. In addition, medioventral process of pygofer is subtriangular. Phallobase separated from aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
