<subSubSection id="C3136563FFA0AE67AE8F62C1FBA8FBE8" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB636E8FFA0AE67AE8F62C1FBEEFED4" blockId="9.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AE8F62C1FB7CFF25" bold="true" box="[199,308,153,179]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Remarks</emphasis>
. In the field, the specimen was tentatively identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ADD062C0FE43FF24" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[920,1035,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ADD062C0FE43FF24" box="[920,1035,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to overall similarity in structure and general habit. More careful morphological examination seemed to confirm generic placement. The general form and behavior of this taxon appeared to coincide with 
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AC9562B8F910FF6C" box="[733,856,224,250]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AC9562B8F91CFF6C" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[733,852,224,250]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Haplaxius</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
While differences in terminalia set this species apart from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AF52635CFBC5FE88" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[282,397,260,286]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AF52635CFBC5FE88" box="[282,397,260,286]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it was molecular characterization that made it apparent that observed differences merited genus level designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB636E8FFA0AE67AE8F6315F83BFE61" blockId="9.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
A difference that appears to set 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AC676315F83DFEF0" authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[559,629,333,358]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="n. g.">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AC676315F83DFEF0" box="[559,629,333,358]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E5781FFA0AE67AC356315F8E7FEF1" box="[637,687,333,359]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" rank="genus">n. g.</taxonomicNameLabel>
apart from 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AD7D6314F9E0FEF0" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[821,936,332,358]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AD7D6314F9E0FEF0" box="[821,936,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AA6A6315FE20FEF0" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[1058,1128,333,358]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AA6A6315FE20FEF0" box="[1058,1128,333,358]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the phallus consists of the phallobase that surrounds the base of the aedeagus and projects beneath to subtend it, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AABF6328FF22FE1C" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[1271,1386,368,394]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AABF6328FF22FE1C" box="[1271,1386,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the phallobase envelopes the aedeagus forming a phallotheca. The variation in degree to which the phallobase surrounds the aedeagus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AF0563E1FBDBFE44" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[333,403,441,466]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AF0563E1FBDBFE44" box="[333,403,441,466]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be discerned from the single species described here, but this character appears to be an important difference among the genera.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB636E8FFA0AE67AE8F6058FBA8FBE8" blockId="9.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
The form of the gonostyli also appears different among the genera. The general form of gonostyli in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AB616058FB6CFDA8" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="senso" subSpecies="stricto">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AB616058FB6CFDA8" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius senso stricto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is that of a larger, globular apex in ventral view and in lateral view, the rounded apex is generally visible but usually angled upward. However, many 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ACF36010F966FDF4" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[699,814,584,610]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ACF36010F966FDF4" box="[699,814,584,610]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deviate from this morphological 
<typeStatus id="54B2884AFFA0AE67AAEF6011FE93FDF5" box="[1191,1243,585,611]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">type</typeStatus>
. The illustrations of the 
<typeStatus id="54B2884AFFA0AE67AEA86035FB58FD11" box="[224,272,621,647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AF386035F838FD11" authority="Fowler, 1904" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[368,624,620,647]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AF386035FB9BFD10" box="[368,467,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. laevis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B19FFA0AE67AF936034F838FD11" author="Fowler, W. W." box="[475,624,620,647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" pagination="85 - 124" refId="ref9770" refString="Fowler, W. W. (1904) Order Rhynchota. Suborder Hemiptera-Homoptera. (Continued). Biologia Centrali-Americana, 1, 85 - 124." type="journal article" year="1904">Fowler, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B19FFA0AE67AC376035F950FD11" author="Kramer, J. P." box="[639,792,621,647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" pagination="301 - 389" refId="ref10261" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1979) Taxonomic study of the planthopper genus Myndus in the Americas (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea: Cixiidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 105 (3), 301 - 389." type="journal article" year="1979">Kramer 1979</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 159–162), terminalia exhibit a rounded terminus of the gonostyli in both ventral and lateral views. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ACE460C8F93BFD3C" baseAuthorityName="Van Duzee" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[684,883,656,682]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crudus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ACE460C8F93BFD3C" box="[684,883,656,682]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius crudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the same general form of the gonostyli and aedeagus as 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AF6E60EDFBC2FD58" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[294,394,692,718]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AF6E60EDFBC2FD58" box="[294,394,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and provided a useful comparison (
<figureCitation id="13322A6DFFA0AE67AD6C60ECF921FD59" box="[804,873,692,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1976,2001]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,625,1957]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[165,1422,625,1957]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Terminalia of Haplaxius crudus in ventral view (A) and lateral view (B) terminalia of Myxia gen. n. belinda sp. n. in ventral view (C) and lateral view (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557843" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557843/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The structure of the terminalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AB4960EDFF38FD58" baseAuthorityName="Van Duzee" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[1281,1392,692,718]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crudus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AB4960EDFF38FD58" box="[1281,1392,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. crudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be comparable to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AC446081F827FD64" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[524,623,728,754]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AC446081F827FD64" box="[524,623,728,754]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and serves as a useful morphological template for comparison. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B19FFA0AE67AB7F6080FAAAFC81" author="Caldwell, J. S." pageId="9" pageNumber="74" pagination="203 - 206" refId="ref9416" refString="Caldwell, J. S. (1946) Notes on Haplaxius Fowler with descriptions of new species (Homoptera, Cixiidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 48 (8), 203 - 206." type="journal article" year="1946">Caldwell (1946)</bibRefCitation>
also considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AFEC60A5F85CFC80" baseAuthorityName="Van Duzee" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[420,532,764,790]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crudus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AFEC60A5F85CFC80" box="[420,532,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. crudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AC0060A4F96FFC80" authority="Fennah, 1945" authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1945" box="[584,807,764,790]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Paramyndus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cocois">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AC0060A4F96FFC80" box="[584,807,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Paramyndus cocois</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) similar enough based on general body structure to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ABC960A5FA90FCAC" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ABC960A5FA90FCAC" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to place them in the same genus, suggesting that there were other species that appeared more distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ABC96179FA90FCC8" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ABC96179FA90FCC8" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. laevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AF50611DFBCFFCC8" baseAuthorityName="Van Duzee" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[280,391,836,862]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crudus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AF50611DFBCFFCC8" box="[280,391,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. crudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It had previously been suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AD0B611CF9FEFCC8" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[835,950,836,862]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AD0B611CF9FEFCC8" box="[835,950,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ADAE611CFE77FCC8" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[998,1087,836,862]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myndus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ADAE611CFE77FCC8" box="[998,1087,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Myndus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) “...could be subdivided into a series of genera or subgenera; these divisions would be based primarily upon structural features or variations in the pattern of the male genitalia, especially the aedeagus.” 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B19FFA0AE67ACB461D5F996FC31" author="Kramer, J. P." box="[764,990,909,935]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" pagination="301 - 389" refId="ref10261" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1979) Taxonomic study of the planthopper genus Myndus in the Americas (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea: Cixiidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 105 (3), 301 - 389." type="journal article" year="1979">Kramer (1979: 302)</bibRefCitation>
. This represents the first genus-group to be erected associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AF8A61E8F87DFC5C" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[450,565,944,970]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AF8A61E8F87DFC5C" box="[450,565,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on molecular data and morphology. One other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AB4861E8FF3BFC5C" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[1280,1395,944,970]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AB4861E8FF3BFC5C" box="[1280,1395,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ABC961E9FA87FC78" baseAuthorityName="Kramer" baseAuthorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ABC961E9FA87FC78" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. delta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, according to Kramer (1977) possesses a similar form for both the gonostyli (bifurcated with dorsal process angled dorsad) and medioventral process (subtriangular). Also, the aedeagus is simple with hooked flagellum and phallobase bearing large processes according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B19FFA0AE67ACF66645F928FBA1" author="Kramer, J. P." box="[702,864,1053,1079]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" pagination="301 - 389" refId="ref10261" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1979) Taxonomic study of the planthopper genus Myndus in the Americas (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea: Cixiidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 105 (3), 301 - 389." type="journal article" year="1979">Kramer (1979</bibRefCitation>
; Fig. 175–179). Based on the overall similarity of the terminalia to the novel taxon we propose 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ACC66619F8A0FBCC" baseAuthorityName="Kramer" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[654,744,1088,1114]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ACC66619F8A0FBCC" box="[654,744,1088,1114]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">H. delta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
be moved to the novel taxon, bringing the species number for 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AEDF663DFA95FBE8" authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,221,1125,1150]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AEDF663DFA95FBE8" box="[151,221,1125,1150]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AEAC663DFB7BFBE9" bold="true" box="[228,307,1125,1151]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24E5781FFA0AE67AEAC663DFB7BFBE9" box="[228,307,1125,1151]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
to two species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136563FFA0AE67AE8F66D1F9FDFB50" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB636E8FFA0AE67AE8F66D1F9FDFB50" blockId="9.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AE8F66D1FB06FB35" bold="true" box="[199,334,1161,1187]" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is an arbitrary amalgamation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67ADD966D0FE4CFB34" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1904" box="[913,1028,1160,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67ADD966D0FE4CFB34" box="[913,1028,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Haplaxius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AA7466D0FEDDFB34" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[1084,1173,1160,1186]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myndus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AA7466D0FEDDFB34" box="[1084,1173,1160,1186]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Myndus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
suggestive of the similarities of 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D6BFFA0AE67AF4166F5FB07FB50" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Humphries &amp; Helmick &amp; Goss &amp; Ascunce" authorityYear="2019" box="[265,335,1197,1222]" class="Bivalvia" family="Veneridae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEAFAFFA0AE67AF4166F5FB07FB50" box="[265,335,1197,1222]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to both genera. The genus name is feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
